Package: shiva-toolkit
Version: 1.0.0-1
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Taran Keval Singh <231631186+tarankeval@users.noreply.github.com>
Depends: bash, coreutils, iproute2, procps, util-linux
Recommends: sudo, smartmontools
Homepage: https://github.com/tarankeval/shiva-toolkit
Description: Extensible Linux server health and maintenance toolkit
 Shiva Toolkit provides a small command-line toolkit for Debian and Ubuntu
 servers. It includes profile-driven health checks, SMART diagnostics,
 network and VPN checks, Docker visibility, logs, backups, updates, and a
 doctor command for troubleshooting.
